'''Malia O Ka Malu''' or '''Our Lady of Peace''' is an appellation of the [[Blessed Virgin Mary]] in the [[Hawaiian language]]. It is shortened from "Malia o ka Malu Hale Pule Nui", a title of the [[mother church]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Honolulu]], the [[Cathedral of Our Lady of Peace]].<ref name=Santoro>{{cite book |last=Santoro |first=Nicholas J. |date= 2011-08-12 |title=Mary In Our Life: Atlas of the Names and Titles of Mary, The Mother of Jesus, and Their Place in Marian Devotion |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=ZXWRgP-0KBkC&pg=PA106&lpg=PA106&dq=Malia+O+Ka+Malu&source=bl&ots=ZRsTZgZhsd&sig=cbYJwcMgYSZIiQvim9I2UMw6RGI&hl=en |publisher=iUniverse |location= |access-date=2016-06-16 | archiveurl= | archivedate= | quote= }}</ref>{{rp|106}}{{cn|date=June 2016}}
Other Hawaiian churches honoring the [[Virgin Mary|Virgin]] include
* [[Maria Lanakila Catholic Church|Maria Lanakila]], ''Our Lady of Victory'', in [[Lahaina, Hawaii|Lahaina]]<ref name=Santoro />{{rp|111}}{{cn|date=June 2016}}
* Malia Hoku O Ke Kai, ''Mary the Star of the Sea'', in [[Kāhala, Hawaii|Kahala]]{{cn|date=June 2016}}
* Malia Puka O Ka Lani, ''Mary the Gate of Heaven'', in [[Hilo, Hawaii|Hilo]]{{cn|date=June 2016}}

